		</div>
		<div class="comment_text"><p>I'm always amazed when I hear companies wanting to see a candidate's code samples! Unless the candidate is active in the open source community (an admirable activity, to be sure) then anything they've written is almost certainly someone else's intellectual property and absolutely could not be shared with another company.</p><p>There's also the danger than in order to satisfy this (in my opinion silly) demand for code samples, candidates will actually grab some random bit of open source code and offer it up as their own. Think that doesn't happen? I was contacted recently by a hiring manager (at some company I don't even remember - so don't ask!) who had just received a code sample from a candidate... a piece of code *I* wrote and released as open source!</p></div>
